Docker is a tool to package apps with all dependencies into containers.

A container is a lightweight, isolated environment (like a mini virtual machine).

Helps in easy deployment and consistency across environments.

Docker Commands:
1.  yum update
2.  yum install docker -y
3.  docker --version
4.  service docker start
5.  docker info
6.  docker pull ubuntu
7.  docker images
8.  docker ps -a
9.  docker run redis
10. docker images
11. docker run alpine
12. docker ps -a
13. docker ps
14. docker run -it ubuntu
15. docker ps
16. docker images
17. docker ps -a
18. docker start jovial_show
19. docker start jovial_showe5e12eee9e37
20. docker ps
21. docker start nostalgic_jang~
22. docker start awesome_lumiere
23. docker attach awesome_lumiere
24. docker ps
25. docker attach awesome_lumiere


